docs.abstract: Humans help train artificial intelligence, so someone may be listening to what you tell Siri, Google Assistant or Alexa. Here’s what to do if you have a problem with that.
docs.snippet: Humans help train artificial intelligence, so someone may be listening to what you tell Siri, Google Assistant or Alexa. Here’s what to do if you have a problem with that.
docs.lead_paragraph: Many of us ask the digital companions in our homes, whether it’s Amazon’s Alexa, Apple’s Siri or Google Assistant, to handle innocuous tasks like setting a timer and playing music.

headline.main: Hi, Alexa. How Do I Stop You From Listening In On Me?
headline.print_headline: Alexa, Please Stop Listening In on Me?

docs.abstract: From Lyndon Johnson to Richard Nixon, presidents have long had fraught relationships with Fed chairs.
docs.snippet: From Lyndon Johnson to Richard Nixon, presidents have long had fraught relationships with Fed chairs.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump has made heckling the Federal Reserve, and its chair, Jerome H. Powell, something of a sport. He has berated Mr. Powell for raising interest rates and taking steps to end a crisis-era stimulus program, likening the Fed to a powerful golfer who has “no touch” and cannot win.

headline.main: Trump’s Feud With the Fed Is Escalating, and Has a Precedent
headline.print_headline: A History of Fraught Presidential Relationships With the Fed

docs.abstract: The president, in a pair of tweets, said he would nominate Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, and Christopher Waller, a St. Louis Fed official, to sit on the Fed board.
docs.snippet: The president, in a pair of tweets, said he would nominate Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, and Christopher Waller, a St. Louis Fed official, to sit on the Fed board.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, who has spent months assailing the Federal Reserve for its interest rate policies, said he planned to nominate Christopher Waller, a longtime regional Fed official, and Judy Shelton, a Fed critic, to serve on the central bank’s seven-member board.

headline.main: Trump Taps Two Fed Nominees, One Conventional, the Other Not
headline.print_headline: Trump Picks Fed Veteran And Fed Critic for Board

docs.abstract: The Texas tycoon’s case on trade anticipated Donald Trump’s arguments two decades later.
docs.snippet: The Texas tycoon’s case on trade anticipated Donald Trump’s arguments two decades later.
docs.lead_paragraph: Ross Perot, who died Tuesday, has not been much in the news in the past few years. But his ideas surely have. His staunch opposition to the North American Free Trade Agreement in the 1990s found a powerful echo two decades later when Donald Trump ran for the presidency calling for a wall on the Mexican border and dismissing Nafta as “perhaps the worst trade deal ever made.”

headline.main: Ross Perot’s Warning of a ‘Giant Sucking Sound’ on Nafta Echoes Today
headline.print_headline: Trade Skeptic, ‘Well Ahead Of His Time’

docs.abstract: Federal Reserve officials were split over what to do when they meet this month. The central bank’s thinking will be clearer this week.
docs.snippet: Federal Reserve officials were split over what to do when they meet this month. The central bank’s thinking will be clearer this week.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Federal Reserve’s meeting this month was never going to be an easy one given that officials remain split over when — or whether — to cut interest rates. The last few weeks could set the Fed up for an even more difficult call.

headline.main: Fed, Pressed by Trump to Cut Rates, Faces Fire No Matter What It Does
headline.print_headline: Fed Faces Fire No Matter What It Does
